   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Feature Adoption Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes user-level product usage data to study adoption rates of key features, segment adoption by user type, and identify which features drive engagement.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Measure feature adoption rates across a user base.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Segment adoption by user type, plan, and tenure.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify features correlated with high engagement and retention.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Generate product development prioritization insights.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Product teams invest heavily in building features, but many go underutilized. Understanding adoption patterns helps prioritize feature investment and identify onboarding gaps.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Features that users adopt drive stickiness. Features that go unused represent wasted engineering investment.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **3,000 users** with adoption flags for 8 features plus engagement metrics.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 3000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"FEATURES = [\\\"Dashboard\\\", \\\"Reports\\\", \\\"API\\\", \\\"Mobile App\\\", \\\"Notifications\\\", \\\"Integrations\\\", \\\"Collaboration\\\", \\\"Advanced Search\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PLANS = [\\\"Free\\\", \\\"Pro\\\", \\\"Enterprise\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"USER_TYPES = [\\\"Individual\\\", \\\"Team\\\", \\\"Admin\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Feature adoption probabilities by plan\\n\",\n",
    "    \"adoption_probs = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Free\\\":       [0.80, 0.30, 0.05, 0.40, 0.50, 0.10, 0.15, 0.20],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Pro\\\":        [0.90, 0.65, 0.30, 0.60, 0.70, 0.40, 0.50, 0.45],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Enterprise\\\": [0.95, 0.85, 0.60, 0.70, 0.80, 0.70, 0.75, 0.65],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plan = rng.choice(PLANS, p=[0.45, 0.35, 0.20])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    user_type = rng.choice(USER_TYPES, p=[0.50, 0.35, 0.15])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tenure = int(rng.exponential(8) + 1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    probs = adoption_probs[plan]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    adopted = {feat: int(rng.random() < prob) for feat, prob in zip(FEATURES, probs)}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    n_adopted = sum(adopted.values())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    logins_30d = max(0, int(rng.normal(5 + n_adopted * 2, 3)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    engagement_score = np.clip(n_adopted / len(FEATURES) * 0.6 + logins_30d / 30 * 0.4 + rng.normal(0, 0.05), 0, 1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    row = {\\\"user_id\\\": f\\\"U{i+1:05d}\\\", \\\"plan\\\": plan, \\\"user_type\\\": user_type,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"           \\\"tenure_months\\\": tenure, \\\"logins_30d\\\": logins_30d,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"           \\\"engagement_score\\\": round(engagement_score, 3), \\\"features_adopted\\\": n_adopted}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    row.update(adopted)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append(row)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Overall feature adoption rates\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"adoption_rates = df[FEATURES].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"adoption_rates.plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=ax, color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Feature Adoption Rate (% of users)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Adoption Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i, v in enumerate(adoption_rates.values):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.text(v + 0.01, i, f\\\"{v:.0%}\\\", va=\\\"center\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Adoption by plan\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"plan_adoption = df.groupby(\\\"plan\\\")[FEATURES].mean().reindex([\\\"Free\\\", \\\"Pro\\\", \\\"Enterprise\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.heatmap(plan_adoption, annot=True, fmt=\\\".0%\\\", cmap=\\\"YlGn\\\", ax=ax, linewidths=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Feature Adoption Rate by Plan\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Feature adoption vs engagement\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"features_adopted\\\", y=\\\"engagement_score\\\", ax=axes[0], palette=\\\"viridis\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Engagement Score by Features Adopted\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Correlation of each feature with engagement\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feat_corr = df[FEATURES + [\\\"engagement_score\\\"]].corr()[\\\"engagement_score\\\"].drop(\\\"engagement_score\\\").sort_values()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feat_corr.plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Feature vs Engagement Correlation\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].axvline(0, color=\\\"black\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Statistical Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"r, p = stats.pearsonr(df[\\\"features_adopted\\\"], df[\\\"engagement_score\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Correlation (features adopted vs engagement): r={r:.3f}, p={p:.2e}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Significant: {p < 0.05}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Dashboard is universally adopted** (~85%+) — it's the core product entry point.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **API and Integrations have the lowest adoption** — expected, as these are power-user features.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Enterprise users adopt significantly more features** than Free users.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Features adopted strongly correlates with engagement score** — each additional feature increases stickiness.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Notifications and Mobile App are mid-adoption** — opportunities for targeted onboarding.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Binary adoption flags miss usage depth/frequency.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data; real products have more complex adoption curves.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No time-to-adoption data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Focus onboarding on getting users to adopt 3+ features (the engagement inflection point).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Create guided tutorials for Reports and Collaboration features for Free users.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Track time-to-first-use for each feature to identify adoption friction.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. A/B test feature discovery prompts to increase adoption of underused features.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Building new features when existing ones are underadopted.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Measuring adoption as binary when usage depth matters.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Not segmenting by plan or user type.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Assuming low adoption means low value — it may mean poor discoverability.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Build a feature adoption funnel — what's the typical adoption sequence?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Cluster users by adoption pattern and profile each cluster.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Calculate the marginal engagement lift of each feature.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Simulate the impact of increasing Mobile App adoption by 20%.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Feature count is the strongest engagement driver** — focus on breadth of adoption.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Free users are significantly underserved** in adoption — onboarding improvements could lift conversion.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Power features (API, Integrations) are niche but critical for Enterprise retention.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
